      <hedline>
        <hl1>Ethical Politics, And Intellectual</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Anand Giridharadas letter comments on Anthony Lewis's August 5 Op-Ed column praising courage and independence of former Pres Gerald Ford</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Anthony Lewis speaks of ''the courage and independence'' of Gerald R. Ford, a president whose respect for the law elevated him from the political rumblings of the day (column, Aug. 5).</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Anthony Lewis speaks of ''the courage and independence'' of Gerald R. Ford, a president whose respect for the law elevated him from the political rumblings of the day (column, Aug. 5).</p>
        <p>But what does it say about our country's choice in leadership when the only president able to transcend politics -- at least in recent memory -- is also the only one never to be elected by the people?</p>
        <p>ANAND GIRIDHARADAS  Chevy Chase, Md., Aug. 5, 2000</p>
      </block>
